headline: Airline stocks fall after Israel attack on Iran closes airspaces
summary: Shares of the airliners are moving lower after Israel’s attack on Iran closed down airspaces across the Middle East. Crude oil prices also spiked as a result of the attacks. Publicly traded companies in the airlines space include Alaska Air (ALK), American Airlines (AAL), Delta Air Lines (DAL), JetBlue (JBLU), Southwest (LUV), Spirit Airlines (SAVE) and United Airlines (UAL).
